OL,6,F"I think many young people had all
OL,7,Ftheir routines and rhythms upset when
OL,8,Fthey returned to school.
OL,10,F"What we've got to do is work with
OL,11,Fthem to better understand why we have
OL,12,Fthese routines, what the rhythms of a
OL,13,Fschool day are, and how it's important
OL,14,Fthat we work together in a society to
OL,15,Fmake sure they can learn - but also so
OL,16,Fthat teachers can do their jobs
OL,17,Fwithout being threatened or upset.
